description.4: Deathlok is transported to the year 1976! After an encounter with Godwulf, Luther Manning finds himself in hot water. In 1976, Deathlok is immediately attacked by the Devil-Slayer who assumes he was sent by "The Cult." When Deathlok sees Cory Payne, Devil-Slayer's wife, he is shocked to discover that she is the mirror-image of his ex-wife Janice Manning!
description.5: It's the Invaders against the Crusaders in a battle to the death!
description.7: The stresses of life have caught up to Howard the Duck. So Howard seeks professional help to get back on track.
description.8: With the help of electro biologist Marla Madison, J. Jonah Jameson launches his Spider-Slayer robot into battle with the wall-crawler. But with J. Jonah Jameson calling the shots, the Spider-Slayer has a less than satisfactory performance. A super-powered being named Will O' the Wisp begins terrorizing New York, while Harry Osborn receives a visit from his psychiatrist Barton Hamilton. Who is Will O' the Wisp? And what effect will his powers of hypnosis have over Spider-Man?
description.9: Wonder Man versus the Vision! Witness a true battle between brawn and telekinetic sentient energy.
description.10: Captain America is on the hunt for a village along the Rio De Muerte when he is attacked by a vicious waterborne monster!
description.12: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.
description.13: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.

description.15: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.
description.16: Sir Wilfred of Ivanhoe chooses his own ruler for England, and pursues the love of his life, in this medieval adaptation of Sir Walter Scott's novel.
description.17: The Enforcer enlists the Water Wizard to end Ghost Rider once and for all!
description.18: Zuras investigates the true nature of the Celestials, when he suddenly makes a shocking discovery! Meanwhile, Thena suddenly abandons Kro along with two captives! What secret agenda is she hiding?
description.19: The Hulk is trapped in a mind game as he does battle with Maha Yogi and Doctor Druid!
description.20: It was inevitable! The Gaurdsman has returned, and he's out for Iron Man's head! Will the Gaurdsman have his revenge? Or will Iron Man defeat the mad villain before it's too late!
description.22: The Asgardians and Thor come across the Grey Gargoyle and his pirate ship and find themselves at his mercy!
description.23: Son of Dracula has been born! Is this an opportunity for someone to betray Dracula?!
description.24: What if the Hulk had the brain of Bruce Banner?
description.25: The X-Men are dispatched from Muir Island in a hoverboat. However, when the boat crashes theyThe X-Men have returned to the United States from Muir Island and have caught someone lurking in their headquarters run into their oldest enemy...
description.26: Sue begins to suspect her husband is not who he seems. Meanwhile, Reed Richards of Earth is trapped in Annihilus' fortress, where the villain reveals a few plans of his own!
description.34: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.
description.35: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.
description.36: MAR-VELL, YOU STAND ACCUSED! The Kree's two mightiest champions clash at long last! Captain Mar-Vell vs. Ronan the Accuser! To the victor -- Earth!
description.38: Mr. Hyde…a god? The man behind the menagerie has the opportunity to take a serum that will give him omnipotent strength!
description.39: The A.I.M. assault continues when a routine rocket launch at NASA turns ugly--because the Doomsday Man strikes! But even if Carol can survive, how will she react when she learns that SHE is Ms. Marvel?
description.41: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.

description.43: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.
description.44: Jim Hawkins joins the crew of the infamous Long John Silver in this illustrated adaptation of Robert Louis Stevenson's classic!
description.47: Spider-Man in Space! Spider-Man has powers aplenty, but much like us, he cannot breathe in space. This may be his demise. Unless...Adam Warlock swoops in for the rescue! What cosmic team-up awaits?
description.48: The Invaders are overtaken by a band of do-gooders calling themselves the Crusaders!
description.50: Stressed out, Howard begins experiencing super hero-themed night terrors. Guest starring Spider-Man, Doctor Strange and other major heroes!
description.51: Spidey finds himself pitted against two reptilian men; Stegron the Dinosaur Man, and the Lizard! After Stegron gets a hold of his "revitalization ray", skeletal dinosaurs are restored to flesh and blood! Spider-Man vs. dinosaurs on the streets of New York City!
description.52: A stone version of the Black Knight bursts into Avengers Mansion swearing revenge. See the epic show down that may put a few Avengers out of commission.
description.53: After his plane crashes in the jungle, Cap is hunted by the Swine!
description.54: Black Goliath and the Champions must subdue Stilt-Man after the villain snags a prized possession! But when the Stranger bursts through the walls of Champions HQ, the team has an even direr problem on their hands!
description.55: Just as the Celestials reveal their existence to the people of earth, they launch an all-out attack on the Deviant kingdom Lemuria! Will Thena choose love over loyalty and side with Kro against her own people?
description.56: Hulk battles the Absorbing Man...on the first day of his new job! In New Mexico, it's splitsville for Betty and Glenn Talbot. What went wrong?
description.57: It's the battle of his life! Can Tony Stark muster the power to take down Ultimo for good? Plus: is this Tony Stark's last battle as Iron Man? Find out the shocking conclusion to Iron Man's showdown with Ultimo!
description.58: James-Michael and Omega are faced with a new, menacing villain on the streets of New York City!
description.59: What is the mystery behind Sporr and is he truly an enemy to Thor and the Asgardians?
description.60: Every lord needs an heir...the birth of the Son of Dracula!
description.61: The Fantastic Four get the "Italian job" treatment when they're unable to stop members of the Maggia led by Top Man. Can the FF reclaim the Baxter Building before they're sent to swim with the fishes?
description.68: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.
description.73: Spider-Woman’s first appearance! Jessica Drew bursts onto the scene in a deadly confrontation with Nick Fury. Her strange origin, and ties to Hydra, revealed!
description.74: Doctor Stephen Strange reflects on his past as a surgeon…and his foray into the Mystic Arts!
description.75: Featuring Nova! After escaping Bullseye’s clutches, Daredevil is thrown into battle against Cobra and Mr. Hyde!
description.76: Still plagued by mysterious headaches and fainting spells, Carol barely has time to seek medical help when the Destructor attacks! Can Ms. Marvel stop both this new foe and a revitalized Scorpion?
description.77: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.
description.78: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.
description.79: Adapting the sci-fi classic novel by H.G. Wells! Humanity braces for their final hour!
description.80: Our heroes struggle when meeting "The Maker of Death!"
description.84: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.
description.88: Ghost Rider: Johnny Blaze makes a mad dash escape! Will Karen Page say “yes” to Johnny’s offer?
description.89: Former lovers Kro and Thena try and bring back their lost love in the Deviant underwater kingdom of Lemuria! Their first date? A Deviant purification ritual, just a bit less romantic than you might think...
description.90: Just as Bruce Banner starts a new life for himself in New York, the Absorbing Man returns to defeat the Hulk! Doc Samson finds a suspicious individual at the Gamma Base.
description.91: The invincible Iron Man takes on Ultimo, death in robotic form! With Ultimo sights set on the nation's capital, only the Armored Avenger stands between him and our country's ultimate destruction!
description.93: Thor's quest to find the missing Odin may come at a high cost as Sporr claims Sif. And the God of Thunder is powerless to stop it!
description.94: Deacon Frost! Blade! Hannibal King! Will Dracula be the one to lead his rivals to destroy one another?
description.95: What if Spider-Man joined the Fantastic Four?
description.96: Following his defeat at the hands of Black Tom and the Juggernaut, Nightcrawler's unconscious body is pulled through the secret passageways of Cassidy Keep by a group of Leprechauns. When Nightcrawler awakens, he is finds himself surrounded by creatures that he thought were creatures of myth...
description.97: Reed Richards takes on the unfamiliar role of villain- will his teammates discover his intentions before it's too late? Featuring Tigra!

0.text: The Human Rocket faces off against the magnificent Megaman! No, not that one!

1.text: Spider-Man and Thing find themselves on board Thanos’s ship and besieged by his legions. Meanwhile, Adam Warlock reunites with Gamora and Pip the Troll within the Soul Gem.

2.text: Super hero meets super-spy as the Thing joins forces with NICK FURY and S.H.I.E.L.D.! But will they be overwhelmed by the tech-wizardry of the FIXER and the mental power and control of MENTALLO?

6.text: Amid Doctor Strange's announcement that he's leaving the group, the new and remaining members try to persuade the Hulk not to follow suit.

16.text: Sir Wilfred of Ivanhoe chooses his own ruler for England, and pursues the love of his life, in this medieval adaptation of Sir Walter Scott’s novel.

21.text: Take a dive into the Marvel Universe of the 1950s! Witness the origin of one of the most bizarre heroes of all time -- the 3-D MAN!

27.text: The Vulture may prove to be too strong for young Spidey, as the wall-crawler struggles desperately in "Spider-Kill"!

28.text: Trapped in the stronghold of their enemies, the Inhumans go wild!

29.text: Sir Denis Nayland Smith calls a meeting of his surviving agents in the wake of James Larner’s funeral.

32.text: Thunderbolt’s tragic backstory reveals why he turned to vigilantism. Goldbug frames Power Man for the theft of a gold shipment…will Cage be able to talk his way out of this one without a punch thrown?

33.text: The conclusion of how the hero called Starhawk came to be!

36.text: MAR-VELL, YOU STAND ACCUSED! The Kree's two mightiest champions clash at long last! Captain Mar-Vell vs. Ronan the Accuser! To the victor -- Earth!

37.text: Hatch-22 is a creature out of time- and he’s not happy about it! Princess Zanda aligns herself with Panther and Abner Little to see Hatch-22 returned to the ‘Sixth Era of Man.’ But will Panther and company find the second Brass Frog in time? Black Panther will need to go to King Solomon's tomb to set right the wrongs unleashed by a dangerous artifact!

38.text: Mr. Hyde…a god? The man behind the menagerie has the opportunity to take a serum that will give him omnipotent strength!

39.text: The A.I.M. assault continues when a routine rocket launch at NASA turns ugly--because the Doomsday Man strikes! But even if Carol can survive, how will she react when she learns that SHE is Ms. Marvel?

40.text: Nova is under the control of the Condor! Are they still working against the Sphinx, or do the villains have their own agenda?

44.text: Jim Hawkins joins the crew of the infamous Long John Silver in this illustrated adaptation of Robert Louis Stevenson’s classic!

46.text: Iron Fist recruits the Thing to help a noble ruler of a faraway island stave off a coup from a power-hungry general!

49.text: Valkyrie, Red Guardian and Hellcat battle the mystical powers of the Red Rajah!

62.text: If college academics weren't difficult enough during the day, imagine having to defeat the vicious Vulture by night!

64.text: The Werewolf by Night and Iron Man fight for dear life against the Tri-Animan!

65.text: Shang-Chi and Clive Reston aren’t dead under the rubble of a fallen fortress -- they actually are on Fu Manchu's rocket ship! And now Shang-Chi must face his father’s rage!

67.text: An aptly named criminal called ‘Goldbug’, (he steals gold), double-crosses Cage! Meanwhile, a new costumed foe named Thunderbolt may turn out to be an ally…but Power Man’s none the wiser.

69.text: The Wrecking Crew crashes the New York City scene...quite literally! Alan Cavenaugh reflects on the sins of his past, while Misty Knight finds herself a hostage. Who is the Wrecking Crew really after? Jean Grey and Cyclops of the X-Men cameo!

70.text: Nova’s rogues join forces to destroy Nova! Also featuring the debut of the maniacal Sphinx!

72.text: Enter the Red Skull! Captain America follows a lead during the Avengers’ battle with Attuma. What dark secrets will Cap uncover about his deadliest villain? A usurper to the Latverian throne has everyone fooled into believing he is Doctor Doom. Who is Prince Rudolfo? And why is he so intent on ousting the despotic Doom?

73.text: Spider-Woman’s first appearance! Jessica Drew bursts onto the scene in a deadly confrontation with Nick Fury. Her strange origin, and ties to Hydra, revealed!

74.text: Doctor Stephen Strange reflects on his past as a surgeon…and his foray into the Mystic Arts!

75.text: Featuring Nova! After escaping Bullseye’s clutches, Daredevil is thrown into battle against Cobra and Mr. Hyde!

76.text: Still plagued by mysterious headaches and fainting spells, Carol barely has time to seek medical help when the Destructor attacks! Can Ms. Marvel stop both this new foe and a revitalized Scorpion?

79.text: Adapting the sci-fi classic novel by H.G. Wells! Humanity braces for their final hour!

81.text: Shaka Kharn, the demon warrior, was given life by Fu Manchu -- in order to bring death to his son, Shang-Chi!

85.text: Big Brother continues to wreak havoc on Luke’s life…and now Noah and Claire Temple are caught in the mix too! Armed with a teched-out helicopter, Big Brother’s love of terror may be a force too strong to reckon with.

98.text: The first ever appearance of the "Lightmaster"! After Spidey is temporarily blinded by this foe, he must uncover the new villain's motivations.
